	     <form action=/cgi-bin/mrate.pl name=f108371944524313>
	     <tr><td id=headerrow colspan=2 class=mform valign=top><a name=/db/item.html?fitem=1680&mid=108371944524313>&nbsp;</a><a id=sj href=/db/item.html?fitem=1680&mid=108371944524313>This IS lvl 14 craft</a> <a id=fs8 href=/db/item.html?fitem=1680&mid=108371944524313#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a>
	     <br clear=all><small>Posted @ Tue, May 4th 9:11 PM 2004</small></td></tr>
	     <tr><td valign=top id=fs8 class=mform><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=193766><span id=Sage>Azna</span></a><br><b><span id=Sage>Sage</span></b><br><span id=notbold>101 posts<br><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good [4.28]</td><td valign=top class=mform width=100%><p>the lvl of the craft does not mean the required lvl to make it. It means that is the maximum lvl you can have before you stop getting skillups. So if an item is crafted and has lvl 23 for example, if you have skill of 19 you will be able to successfully make it (with a few failures) and it will raise skill on occasion. HOWEVER once it raises your skill to lvl 23 you will no longer gain skill ups from this item. You can make 200 in a row and you will never see a skill up. At this point you hafta move on to a higher lvl, and thus more difficult to craft item. Remember, the skill lvl is not what is required to make it, but the farthest it will take you before skill-ups stop :)<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Tue May&nbsp;&nbsp;4 21:14:43 2004</em></p>&nbsp;<br></td></tr>
	     <tr><td colspan=2 align=right class=mform id=fs8>0 Replies</td></tr>
